
{ Duties of a DBA

  A DBA is confronted with some or all of the following tasks;
    • A DBA must understand the architecture of a → development/databases[database].
    • Install, upgrade and patch database software.
    • Create the database
    • Develop and test a *backup and recovery* strategy
    • Put backup strategy to work
    • Manage storage
    • Security
    • Performance tuning
    • Evaluate new database features


}
